The paper also discusses the use of sparse coding and regularization, which are techniques commonly used in the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper presents experimental results that show the effectiveness of the proposed method, which is a topic commonly studied in the sub-category of cs.SD (Sound).
